<section class="section" aria-labelledby="goals-title">
  <header class="section-header">
    <h2 class="section-title" id="goals-title">Goals</h2>
  </header>
  
  <div class="grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Fluency without reference</h3>
      <p>Write Day 1–15 programs from memory. No syntax lookup. Variables, loops, functions, arrays — automatic.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Multi-file comfort</h3>
      <p>Organize code across .h/.cpp pairs. CMake builds. Header guards. Forward declarations. Link-time thinking.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Debugging instinct</h3>
      <p>Day 6: inject 5 bug classes. Fix all. Log why each happened. Build the mental catalog: "this symptom → that cause."</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>STL as default</h3>
      <p>Vectors over arrays. Algorithms over raw loops. Iterators over indices. <code>std::string</code> over char*. RAII everywhere.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Class design discipline</h3>
      <p>Private data. Constructors enforce invariants. Getters only when needed. No anemic structs with logic outside.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>PID intuition</h3>
      <p>Explain P/PI/PID behavior on a plant without equations. Tune by feel. Recognize overshoot, steady-state error, oscillation.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Retrieval habit</h3>
      <p>Study solved → close → write blank → diff → annotate. Every day. The diff is the test. The log is the grade.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Ship Day 30</h3>
      <p>Student Management System: menu-driven, multi-file, validated I/O, vector storage, class hierarchy, search/sort/stats. Clean enough to hand to a teammate.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>